[16:32:24] == Blue wins battle 1 by attrition after 33 turns ==  (match R 0-1 B)
[16:32:30] red notes: Frustrating—I clawed back to 5-2 with a good Artillery kill mid-game, but Blue's tight support chains around D3/D4 made every late-game attack mathematically losing, and I spent my final cards repositioning units instead of converting damage. Should've deployed more aggressively while I had reserve Infantry left.
[16:32:35] blue notes: Battle 1 felt like a recovery—I overextended early with Cavalry deployments and got punished hard (lost 4 VP in one swing), but pivoted to grinding out a VP advantage through careful Artillery placement and trading efficiently. By the endgame, it became a pure math game: I just needed to reach 3 VP (matching Red's reserve ceiling) and hold it until Red's deck ran out, which I did.
