[16:44:45] == Blue wins battle 2 by attrition after 33 turns ==  (match R 0-2 B)
[16:44:50] red notes: Strong start with a 5-2 lead after aggressive Cavalry deployment and killing Blue's Artillery, but I hemorrhaged units in the mid-game through bad card draws and positioning errors that left my Infantry isolated and unsupported. By turn 23 I was down to 2 VP struggling to rebuild, and by the end Blue's concentrated 4-Infantry force overwhelmed my remnants—I went from winning the attrition race to losing 0-4 in the span of a dozen turns.
[16:44:55] blue notes: Battle 2 felt like a comeback—I started strong but got crushed when Red's Artillery deploy sent me down 1 vs 6 VP. The Mass Assault play that eliminated Red's Artillery was the inflection point; from there it was a disciplined grind through the long map, trading tenaciously and leveraging card advantage to build back to a commanding 4 vs 0 finish.
